    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-12-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-12-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="228"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d228">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-12-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 20, 1901</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my dispatch No. 721, I have received letter from Lilly-white’s
                    counsel, inclosing one from him accepting the sum offered. Shall I inform
                    foreign office that we accept the proposed settlement of the claim, ask for the
                    amount, and hand it over to Lillywhite, who seems anxious for money?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">White.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
